---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const sections = [
  {
    id: 'information-we-may-ask-you-to-provide',
    title: 'I. Information We May Ask You to Provide',
    body: `
<p>Through our LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, we collect information about you and/or your student when you choose to provide it to us. You may share details in order to use LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, purchase products, request information, apply for a role, register for programs, or verify age. In general, we may ask you for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Contact information such as name, email address, mailing address, and phone numbers (note to parents/guardians of children: if we know a user is under 13, we ask for parent or guardian involvement);</li>
  <li>Month, day, and year of birth;</li>
  <li>Gender preference;</li>
  <li>Course interests;</li>
  <li>Billing information such as credit card number and billing address;</li>
  <li>User names to third-party systems (for example, Facebook);</li>
  <li>Information shared on forums or chat rooms within our LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services (note to parents/guardians of children: forums and chat rooms allow a child user to share personal information that would be visible to other users);</li>
  <li>Information included in resumes and job applications; and</li>
  <li>Health details, participation limitations or needs, immunization status, and allergy information.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Note to parents/guardians:</em> We only collect the information described above from someone we know to be a child after we receive verifiable consent, unless a limited exception applies. See the section titled "Our Commitment to Children's Privacy" for more.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'information-collected-automatically',
    title: 'II. Information Collected Automatically',
    body: `
<p><strong>Cookies and other tracking technologies</strong></p>
<p>We may use cookies, web beacons, pixel tags, log files, Local Storage Objects, or similar technologies to collect information about visitors to and users of LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services. This can include the date and time you visit, the pages you view, the time spent within our sites, how often you return, click-stream data, and emails you open, forward, or click. We may automatically gather your browser and operating system type, Internet Service Provider, IP address, software version, and the domain you used to access LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services. We use this information to monitor and improve LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, support internal operations, personalize your experience, verify e-signatures, and perform internal analysis.</p>
<p>We do not use cookies or similar technologies to track your activities on non-LEAGUE sites or to serve ads based on browsing activities outside of LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services. LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services do not recognize "Do Not Track" headers or similar mechanisms.</p>
<p>Our Sites &amp; Services may use third-party plug-ins to provide additional services. These third parties may collect information about you. When we use a plug-in we identify it and link to the third party's privacy policy. We may also collect geolocation information from your device so we can customize your experience. You can typically disable geolocation collection in your device or app settings.</p>
<p><strong>Social media</strong></p>
<p>You can interact with our content on or through social media services and other third-party platforms. When you do, you may allow us to access certain information in your profile such as name, email, photo, gender, birthday, location, IDs, user files, connections, or posts. Refer to the privacy policies on those services to manage what they share.</p>
<p>If we interact with you through third-party sites, we may receive information about your engagement with our content there, including content viewed and ads clicked.</p>
<p><strong>Information from third-party services</strong></p>
<p>We may obtain information from third parties and combine it with details collected through our Websites. For example, if you log in through a social login or other authentication service, we access information based on that provider's authorization process. You should review privacy settings on third-party services to understand what they share with us.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'control-cookies',
    title: 'III. Your Ability to Control Cookies and Similar Technologies',
    body: `
<p>We use cookies or similar technologies to monitor and improve LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, support internal operations, personalize your experience, support e-signatures, and conduct internal analysis. You can accept or decline cookies. Most browsers accept cookies by default, but you can usually adjust your settings to decline them. Consult your browser's help resources for instructions.</p>
<p>If you decline cookies, some services may not function properly, such as logging in or managing a shopping cart. We do not share cookie data with third parties.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'how-we-use-information',
    title: 'IV. How We May Use Your Information',
    body: `
<p>We may use information collected from and about you and/or your student to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Register you or your student with LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services;</li>
  <li>Provide access to LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services;</li>
  <li>Fulfill orders, process payments, and prevent transactional fraud;</li>
  <li>Respond to requests or inquiries;</li>
  <li>Provide information about our products and services;</li>
  <li>Consider you for employment or volunteer opportunities;</li>
  <li>Register you or your student in programs;</li>
  <li>Verify your student's age;</li>
  <li>Monitor and improve LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, support internal operations, personalize the online experience, and conduct internal analysis;</li>
  <li>Protect the security or integrity of LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services and our business;</li>
  <li>Facilitate the sale or potential sale of our business or assets; or</li>
  <li>Meet legal requirements.</li>
</ul>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'how-we-share-information',
    title: 'V. How We Share Information',
    body: `
<p>We do not sell or share your or your student's information with third parties except for the limited purposes described below. Parents or guardians of children under 13 may consent to collection and use without consenting to disclosure to certain third parties.</p>
<p><strong>1. Law enforcement and safety</strong></p>
<p>We may access, preserve, and/or disclose information collected through LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services if required by law or if we believe it is reasonably necessary to comply with legal process, enforce our Terms and Conditions, respond to claims, protect rights or property, or safeguard personal safety. We may also disclose information to limit legal liability.</p>
<p><strong>2. Service providers</strong></p>
<p>Information may be shared with third parties engaged to deliver services such as housing, meals, payment processing, email distribution, software, or other technical functions. These providers only receive the information needed to perform their duties and agree to maintain confidentiality. Review the policies of third-party providers, such as payment processors, before sharing additional information with them.</p>
<p><strong>3. Business transfer</strong></p>
<p>If we sell or purchase assets, or if another entity acquires us, information collected may be transferred. In bankruptcy or reorganization proceedings, information may be treated as an asset. We will seek to ensure any transferee honors this privacy statement.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'commitment-to-childrens-privacy',
    title: "VI. Our Commitment to Children's Privacy",
    body: `
<p>Protecting children's privacy is paramount. We comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA). Our LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services are intended for general audiences. We do not knowingly allow anyone under 13 to provide personal information without verifiable parental or guardian consent, except where limited exceptions apply, including but not limited to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Collecting a parent or child's contact information solely to provide notice and obtain consent;</li>
  <li>Collecting a parent's contact details to provide voluntary notice about a child's participation when no other personal information is collected;</li>
  <li>Collecting a child's contact information to respond one time to a specific request and deleting it afterward;</li>
  <li>Collecting a child and parent's contact information to respond more than once to a specific request without using it otherwise;</li>
  <li>Collecting contact information to protect a child's safety without using it for unrelated purposes;</li>
  <li>Collecting a persistent identifier solely to support internal operations; or</li>
  <li>Other instances permitted or required by law.</li>
</ul>
<p>If we obtain verifiable consent, we collect, use, and disclose the child's information as described in this statement. Some features, such as forums and chat rooms, allow child users to share comments that may include personal information visible to other users. Parents should advise children of the risks of posting personal information online.</p>
`,
  },
