  {
    id: 'terms-and-conditions',
    title: 'XV. Terms and Conditions',
    body: `
<p>Your use of LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services, and any information you provide, is subject to The LEAGUE of Amazing Programmers Terms and Conditions.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'privacy-statement-changes',
    title: 'XVI. Privacy Statement Changes',
    body: `
<p>We occasionally amend this privacy statement and reserve the right to change, modify, add, or remove portions at any time. If we materially change the use of personal information, we will announce it on relevant LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services and note it in this statement. The effective date appears at the beginning. Questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:info@jointheleague.org">info@jointheleague.org</a> or mailed to 12625 High Bluff Drive #107, San Diego, CA 92130.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'credit-card-information',
    title: 'XVII. Your Credit Card Information and Transactions',
    body: `
<p>For convenience, you can have us bill you or pay by credit card. If you choose credit card payment, we keep the card information on file but do not display it online. Your card security number is not stored in our system.</p>
<p>We use Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption to safeguard transactions. Your information, including credit card data, is encrypted as it travels over the internet.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'social-networking-disclaimer',
    title: 'XVIII. Social Networking Disclaimer',
    body: `
<p>The LEAGUE of Amazing Programmers provides opportunities for social networking on platforms such as Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, Flickr, and YouTube. These sites are not affiliated with The LEAGUE and maintain their own terms and policies. Please read the Terms and Conditions on each platform. These Terms apply whether you are a visitor or a participant on sites with an official LEAGUE affiliation.</p>
<p>When you register for a LEAGUE program, your participant may access social networking sites and can create accounts if they meet the requirements. Interaction guidelines include:</p>
<ul>
  <li>We provide a medium for online socializing, but users are responsible for their interactions.</li>
  <li>We do not screen members or moderate statements beyond platform policies.</li>
  <li>Participants must exercise caution and judgment when sharing personal information.</li>
  <li>Parents should advise participants to take reasonable precautions when interacting with others online or in person.</li>
  <li>Participants must not harass, threaten, bully, stalk, or invade privacy, and must not encourage others to do so.</li>
  <li>Participants should not share social networking information directly with LEAGUE staff, and staff will not share personal contact details.</li>
</ul>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'copyright-and-intellectual-property',
    title: 'XIX. Copyright and Intellectual Property Policy',
    body: `
<p>You and your participant agree not to use social networking sites to offer, display, distribute, transmit, or store material that infringes copyrighted works, trademarks, service marks, or other intellectual property rights. The LEAGUE reserves the right to terminate accounts of users who repeatedly infringe or are believed to infringe the rights of others.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'disclaimer',
    title: 'XX. Disclaimer',
    body: `
<p>By using social networking sites or submitting content, you agree that The LEAGUE of Amazing Programmers is not liable for lost or misdirected submissions, technical errors, communication disruptions, or damages caused by computer viruses or site access. LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services and member submissions are provided "as is" without warranty. Some jurisdictions do not allow certain exclusions, so portions of this disclaimer may not apply.</p>
`,
  },
  {
    id: 'indemnification',
    title: 'XXI. Indemnification',
    body: `
<p>You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold The LEAGUE of Amazing Programmers, its officers, directors, employees, and agents harmless from claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or connected with your access to or use of affiliated social networking sites, your violation of these Terms, your infringement of third-party rights, or any claim that your submitted content caused damage or violated rights.</p>
`,
  },
];

const toc = sections.map(({ id, title }) => ({ id, title }));
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Learn how The League of Amazing Programmers collects, uses, and protects personal information across our sites and services."
>
  <section class="section policy-hero">
    <div class="container policy-hero__content">
      <span class="tag">Policy Center</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>
        Publish Date: 11/03/2020. This privacy policy applies to individuals who visit or use LEAGUE Sites &amp; Services that collect data or display these terms. By using our sites, you agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of data as described.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container policy-intro">
      <p>All references to "us," "we," or "our" refer to The LEAGUE of Amazing Programmers. References to "child" or "children" indicate individuals under 13 years of age.</p>
      <p>By accessing or using any LEAGUE Site or Service, you consent to the terms in this privacy statement.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--surface-alt">
    <div class="container policy-toc">
      <h2>On this page</h2>
      <ul class="policy-toc__list">
        {toc.map((item) => (
          <li><a href={`#${item.id}`}>{item.title}</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  {sections.map((section) => (
    <section class="section policy-detail" id={section.id}>
      <div class="container policy-detail__inner">
        <h2>{section.title}</h2>
        <div class="policy-detail__content" set:html={section.body} />
      </div>
    </section>
  ))}
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy-hero {
    background: var(--color-hero-gradient);
  }

  .policy-hero__content {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .policy-intro {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .policy-toc {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .policy-toc__list {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .policy-toc__list a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .policy-toc__list a:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy-detail__inner {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    max-width: 840px;
  }

  .policy-detail__content {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .policy-detail__content ul,
  .policy-detail__content ol {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .policy-detail__content a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .policy-detail__content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
